Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine light buff-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 51, 8? Name Nikagis. From same die as 1925,0119.781 and probably Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, CEALEX F198.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0781)
